properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 27 at 10:35PM AKST until January 29 at 3:00AM AKST by NWS Juneau AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Southeast winds of 25 to 35 mph with gusts to 60 mph
expected.

* WHERE...Eastern Gulf Coast and Central and Southern Inner
Channels including, Sitka, Ketchikan, Hydaburg, Craig, Thorne
Bay, Point Baker, and Coffman Cove.

* WHEN...Winds will increase rapidly Tuesday evening and peak
around midnight Tuesday night before diminishing early
Wednesday morning.

* IMPACTS...Prepare for power outages. Downed trees and power
lines are possible. Improperly moored boats and aircraft may
break loose from their tie-downs.
properties.instruction:
A high wind warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected
or occurring.
